From c4b4e8a69f862b402b47de54b585d20d70d96c97 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dmitry Kravkov <dmitry@broadcom.com>
Date: Sun, 17 Nov 2013 08:59:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 090/192] bnx2x: Clean the sp rtnl task upon unload

commit a0d307b21025106157709521d5b88831530e2112 upstream

While unloading, bnx2x needs to clean the sp_rtnl_state to prevent
configuration made before the unload to be applied afterwards with
stale values.

Signed-off-by: Dmitry Kravkov <dmitry@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Yuval Mintz <yuvalmin@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Ariel Elior <ariele@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Yunguo Wei <yunguo.wei@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c |    4 ++++
 1 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
index a02fcb3..d707029 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2x/bnx2x_cmn.c
@@ -2951,6 +2951,10 @@ int bnx2x_nic_unload(struct bnx2x *bp, int unload_mode, bool keep_link)
 
 	bp->port.pmf = 0;
 
+	/* clear pending work in rtnl task */
+	bp->sp_rtnl_state = 0;
+	smp_mb();
+
 	/* Free SKBs, SGEs, TPA pool and driver internals */
 	bnx2x_free_skbs(bp);
 	if (CNIC_LOADED(bp))
